cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.DC 

The paper deals with image classification using deep learning techniques, specifically focusing on Zero-Shot Learning (ZSL). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel model for classification, which involves learning class representatives and matching them with new data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Apache Spark for distributed learning and recognition, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with image datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
